    "methodology": "Net migration is the difference between immigration and emigration over a 12-month rolling period, published quarterly by ONS. Figures prior to 2021 are based on the International Passenger Survey; from 2021 they incorporate administrative data (Home Office visa records, NHS registrations, HMRC records) and are not directly comparable. Work and study visa breakdowns are from Home Office visa statistics.",
    "knownIssues": [
      "ONS revised historical net migration estimates significantly upward in 2023 following the shift to administrative data sources; pre-2021 and post-2021 figures use different methodologies",
      "The 2024 figure is provisional and subject to revision; visa restrictions introduced in early 2024 affect student dependants and care worker routes",
      "Net migration does not distinguish between temporary and permanent migration; students and seasonal workers inflate gross flows without representing long-term population change"
